anicCmdTable.name: anicCmdTable
anicCmdTable.description: The NIC Command table contains an entry for each of the manageable Analog Modem NIC entity in the chassis. It provides a means through which to take specific actions on one or more NICs in the NAS chassis.

anicCmdEntry.name: anicCmdEntry
anicCmdEntry.description: There is one NIC Command entry per NIC entity in the chassis.

anicCmdIndex.name: anicCmdIndex
anicCmdIndex.description: A unique value for each manageable Analog Modem NIC entity in the chassis. The value of this object matches the value of the index of the corresponding manageable Analog Modem NIC entity in the entity table of the chassis MIB.

anicCmdMgtStationId.name: anicCmdMgtStationId
anicCmdMgtStationId.description: This object is a generic read-write variable that a Management Station (MS) can use to guarantee that the results from a given command are the results of a command issued by that specific MS. Each MS must SET a unique value to this object when doing commands and GET the value of this object together with amnicCmdReqId and amnicCmdResult to detect interference from other MSs.

anicCmdReqId.name: anicCmdReqId
anicCmdReqId.description: This object contains the value of the request-id field in the SNMP PDU which invoked the current or most recent command or test on this NIC Card. If the request-id is unknown or undefined, this object contains the value zero.

anicCmdFunction.name: anicCmdFunction
anicCmdFunction.description: This object contains a value which describes the command which is being invoked.

anicCmdForce.name: anicCmdForce
anicCmdForce.description: In some cases, the NIC may be in a state such that certain commands could adversely affect connections. In such cases, a command request with this object not present or set to noForce will result in a warning. If the operator elects to ignore such warnings, this object can be set to force in a subsequent issue of the command to cause the command to be carried out regardless of its potentially hazzardous effects.

anicCmdParam.name: anicCmdParam
anicCmdParam.description: This object contains parameters that are specific to the particular command being issued. In some cases, there will be no aditional parameters required.

anicCmdResult.name: anicCmdResult
anicCmdResult.description: This object contains the result of the most recently requested command or test, or the value none(1) if no commands have been requested since the last reset.

anicCmdCode.name: anicCmdCode
anicCmdCode.description: The value of this object upon test completion is dependent on the value of nicCmdFunction used to invoke the command. In the case of action commands, the value of this object is zero if the command was successful, and indicates a further description of what went wrong if it was unsuccessful. In the case of tests, the value here is a bit mapped result of each of the sub-tests performed.

anicCfgTable.name: anicCfgTable
anicCfgTable.description: The NIC Configuration table contains an entry for each entity in the NIC. It provides a means through which to configure an individual entity.

anicCfgEntry.name: anicCfgEntry
anicCfgEntry.description: There is one NIC configure entry per NIC entity in the chassis.

anicCfgIndex.name: anicCfgIndex
anicCfgIndex.description: A unique value for each entity in the Analog Modem NIC card.

anicCfgMdmRingNATrapEna.name: anicCfgMdmRingNATrapEna
anicCfgMdmRingNATrapEna.description: Enable or disable the modem ring no answer event.

anicCfgDteRingNATrapEna.name: anicCfgDteRingNATrapEna
anicCfgDteRingNATrapEna.description: Enable or Disable the DTE ring no answer event.

anicCfgRingThresh.name: anicCfgRingThresh
anicCfgRingThresh.description: Set up the number of ring threshold for the ring no answer events.

anicCfgLineStatus.name: anicCfgLineStatus
anicCfgLineStatus.description: This object is used to specify the line status.
